        "justification": "The original contract explicitly states that ENVISION is not an agent of SIERRA for any purpose, including federal tax purposes. The changed text directly contradicts this by designating ENVISION as an agent of SIERRA for marketing and sales purposes. The Law Explanation indicates that agency relationships involve a level of control that conflicts with independent contractor status. While the scraped snippets are not helpful here, the alteration clearly introduces an agency relationship where there was none, undermining the independent contractor status initially established in the agreement, hence creating a contradiction under the definition of Misaligned Terminology Legal Contradiction."
